         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">14/10/88. ¶  ¶ Allow me, dear Prof. Watson, to draw your attention to the fact, that — (as you will soon see in the Key to the syst. of Vict. pl. ¶ ) the Jussieua, called by Mr. Bentham J. repens in t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.10.14</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Sereno Watson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Gray Herbarium Archives, Harvard University, Cambridge, Massachusetts.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">14/10/88.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me, dear Prof. Watson, to draw your attention to the fact, that — (as you will soon see in the Key to the syst. of Vict. pl.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B88.11.02, p. 254.</p>
               </note>) the Jussieua, called by Mr. Bentham J. repens in the Flora Austral.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham (1863-78), vol. 3, p. 306.</p>
               </note> is the J. diffusa of Forskael,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Forsskål.</p>
               </note> as I have found out. It differs from the S. Asiatic J. repens <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">L</hi>
               </seg>. in smaller flowers, in petals entirely yellow not largely white, in only diminutive natatory apparatus and in some other particulars.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now in all probability the W. American floating Jussieua is also identical with the African not the Asiatic species. So it would be of interest, to reinvestigate this subject, for which you have probably ample material there. When at the Murray-River<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">SA.</p>
               </note> in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">1848</hi>
               </seg> I saw already, that the Austr. sp. could not be identical with the Indian, and gave it then the temporary name J. australis, under which it was distributed in my earlier collections.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MEL 2208441 was collected by M in SA, 'Fluitans in fl. Murray haud procula Mount Beevor' [Floating in the Murray River not far from Mount Beevor] in February 1848, M's label from that time naming it as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">J. australasica</seg>. A later label of M's identifies it as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">J. diffusa</seg>.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Please remember me to the excellent Profs Trelease &amp; Sargent.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Did you see the proof-slips of the Key,<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B86.04.05 (pt. 2) and B88.11.02 (pt. 1).</p>
               </note> regularly sent to your Department or rather our lamented friend Asa Gray, and after his death to Prof. Sargent.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Jussieua%20australis">Jussieua australis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Jussieua%20diffusa">Jussieua diffusa</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Jussieua%20repens">Jussieua repens</name>
            </p>
         </div>
